This paper deals with clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The focus of the paper is on developing online algorithms for hierarchical clustering, which is a subfield of clustering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the practical applications of clustering, such as natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
